This rule references the Conventional Commits specification. For practical commit message guidelines, see [git-commit.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/git-commit.mdc).

**Commit format:** `<type>[optional scope]: <description>`

**Common types:** `feat`, `fix`, `refactor`, `docs`, `test`, `style`, `chore`, `perf`, `revert`

**Breaking changes:** Use `!` after type/scope or `BREAKING CHANGE:` footer.

Full specification: https://www.conventionalcommits.org/
